          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "PHOTO"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The target was composed, of 10 Ta plates with",
                "a diam. of 4.9 cm and an effective thickness of 7.4 cm",
                "There was a 0.15 cm water gap between Ta plates in",
                "order to cool the target effectively. The housing of",
                "the target was made of titanium. This target was set",
                "at the center of a cylindrical water moderator",
                "contained in an aluminum cylinder with thickness of",
                "0.5 cm, a diam. of 30 cm and height of 30 cm.",
                "The estimated neutron yield per kW of beam power for",
                "electron energies above 60 MeV at the Ta target",
                "is about 1.9 x 10**12 n/s"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The natural W consists of 180W (0.12%), 182W (26.49%),",
                "183W (14.314%), 184W (30.642%) and 186W (28.42%).",
                "Natural W metallic foils, 18 mm x 18 mm in area by",
                "0.2 mm in thickness, were used as the activation",
                "samples. The Au and In foils were used as the",
                "standard reactions and the neutron monitors.",
                "   Characteristics of Hf, Au, and In foils",
                " Foils Size(mm) Weight (mg)  Thickness(mm) Purity(%)",
                "  W    18 x 18  1263.6 +- 0.8    0.2          99.95",
                "       18 x 18  1289.1 +- 0.8    0.2          99.95",
                "  Au   18 x 18   186.3 +- 0.5    0.03         99.95",
                "       18 x 18   188.5 +- 0.5    0.03         99.95",
                "  In   18 x 18   127.6 +- 0.4    0.05         99.99",
                "                 121.7 +- 0.4    0.05         99.99",
                "                 121.4 +- 0.4    0.05         99.99",
                "                 122.0 +- 0.4    0.05         99.99",
                "                 127.1 +- 0.4    0.05         99.99",
                "                 124.5 +- 0.4    0.05         99.99"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 6Li-ZnS(Ag) scintillator BC702 with a diam.",
                "of 127 mm and a thickness of 6.35 mm mounted on an",
                "EMI-93090 photomultiplier was used as a detector for",
                "the neutron TOF spectrum measurement. Scintillator",
                "consists of a matrix of a lithium compound enriched to",
                "95% 6Li dispersed in a fine ZnS(Ag) phosphor powder."
              ]
            }
